#: ../../source/api/prepshot.utils.rst:2
msgid "utils"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:1
msgid "This module contains utility functions for the model."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:3
msgid ""
"Here, we determine factors to covert future value to present value for "
"costs and benefits. To account for the variable factor, fixed factor, and"
" capital factor, we need to convert all future costs to their net present"
" value. This means adjusting for the time value of money so that all "
"costs are expressed in terms of today's dollars."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:9
msgid ""
"We also assume that variable cost and fixed cost for non-modelled years "
"are assumed to be equal to the cost of the last modelled year preceding "
"them. This allows for consistent comparison across different time periods"
" and technologies."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:14
msgid "**Variable Factor**"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:-1
msgid "Calculation of variable costs"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:21 prepshot.utils:63
msgid "Given the following:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:23
msgid "Variable cost of modeled year: :math:`B`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:24 prepshot.utils:67
msgid "Discount rate: :math:`r`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:25 prepshot.utils:68
msgid ":math:`m`-th modeled year: :math:`m = y - y_\\text{min}`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:26
msgid "Depreciation periods: :math:`n`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:28 prepshot.utils:71
msgid "The total present value can be calculated as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:30
msgid ""
"\\begin{align}\n"
"\\text{total present value} &= \\frac{B}{(1+r)^m} + "
"\\frac{B}{(1+r)^{m+1}}\n"
"+ \\cdots + \\frac{B}{(1+r)^{(m+k-1)}} \\\\\n"
"&= B(1+r)^{(1-m)}\\frac{1-(1+r)^k}{r}\n"
"\\end{align}"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:39
msgid "And we can calculate the variable factor as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:41
msgid ""
"\\begin{align}\n"
"\\text{factor}_{y}^{var} &= (1+r)^{1-m_y}\\frac{1-(1+r)^{k_y}}{r} \\\\\n"
"m_{y} &= y - y_\\text{min} \\\\\n"
"k_{y} &= y_\\text{periods}\n"
"\\end{align}"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:50
msgid "**Fixed Factor**"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:52
msgid "We can equate the fixed factor with the variable factor as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:54
msgid ""
"\\text{factor}_{y}^\\text{fix} = factor_{y}^\\text{var}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:56
msgid "**Investment Factor**"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:-1
msgid "Calculation of investment costs"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:65
msgid ""
"Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC, or otherwise known as the "
"interest rate): :math:`i`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:69
msgid "Length of :math:`m`-th planning periods: :math:`k`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:73
msgid ""
"\\begin{align}\n"
"\\text{total present value} &= \\frac{P}{(1+r)^m} \\\\\n"
"&= \\frac{\\frac{A}{(1+i)} + \\frac{A}{(1+i)^2} + \\cdots\n"
"+ \\frac{A}{(1+i)^n}}{(1+r)^m} \\\\\n"
"&= A\\frac{1-(1+i)^{-n}}{i}\\times\\frac{1}{(1+r)^m}\n"
"\\end{align}"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:83
msgid ""
"From the above, we can solve for the annualized cost of depreciation "
"periods, :math:`A`, as:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:86
msgid "A = P\\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:90
msgid "The capital recovery factor is then calculated as:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:92
msgid "\\text{capital recovery factor} = \\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:96
msgid ""
"Let's focus on the time periods that fall within the modelled time "
"horizon (indicated in black colour). We can calculate the length of time "
"periods, :math:`k`, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:100
msgid "k = y_{max} - y"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:104
msgid "Using :math:`k`, we can calculate the net present value as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:106
msgid ""
"\\text{net present value} =\n"
"\\begin{cases}\n"
"\\frac{\\frac{A}{(1+r)} + \\frac{A}{(1+r)^2} + \\cdots\n"
"+ \\frac{A}{(1+r)^{min(n, k)}}}{(1+r)^m} \\text{if} \\quad n \\le k \\\\\n"
"\\text{total present value}\\quad \\text{if }n > k \\\\\n"
"\\frac{A\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-k}}{r}}{(1+r)^m} = "
"P\\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}\\times\n"
"\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-k}}{r(1+r)^m} & \\text{otherwise}\n"
"\\end{cases}"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:117
msgid "And we can calculate the investment factor as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot.utils:119
msgid ""
"factor_{y}^{inv} = \\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}\\times\n"
"\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-min(n,k)}}{r(1+r)^m}"
msgstr ""

